						               													<description>Butterfly Effect is the game of Unintended Consequences. A hilarious game where you put your mind to the test. Can you explain what happened? Use your quick wits and a healthy dose of the ridiculous. Fun for friends and family as you compete to see who can master the CHAOS.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;The Butterfly Effect (also known as Chaos Theory) came from an age old saying - A butterfly flaps its wings in China causing a Tornado in America. This is the idea that a small change can create far reaching ramifications somewhere else.&amp;#10;So how do you play?&amp;#10;It&amp;rsquo;s very easy to play. Each player gets handed out a series of cards:&amp;#10;A Person &amp;#10;An Action &amp;#10;A Start Location &amp;#10;Players take it in turns with the first player putting down 2 cards:&amp;#10;A Disaster &amp;#10;A Destination &amp;#10;The other players then have to select a Person, Action and Start Location set of cards to create a story of how the Disaster happened at the Destination location.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
